verbose_text: No significant reduction of DNA breaks was observed in cells depleted of MFAP1 after transcription inhibition (XREF_FIG A) or after RNase H1 overexpression (XREF_FIG B), in contrast with the suppression observed in cells depleted of THOC1 and other factors that prevent R-loop accumulation, indicating that DNA breaks induced by MFAP1 depletion were not transcription dependent or mediated by R-loops.
